wikipedia_page.main: Dame Joan Margaret Higgins, DBE FAcSS is a British academic, educator, and public health service manager.

response: Dame Joan Higgins chaired the body from 2007 until she stepped down at the end of 2013. Ian Dilks held the post for two three-year terms, from 2014 to 2020.
